This paper proposes a method for improving the accuracy of detecting small objects in images using context and attention mechanisms. The proposed method is based on object detection algorithms and uses additional features from different layers as context. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of attention mechanisms and multi-scale features suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
